The input for the system should strictly be a string.The occurrence count of each vowel ('a', 'e', 'i', 'o', 'u') in the provided string should be determined by the system.The method should identify the longest substring in the parameter string that contains each vowel an even number of times.The length of the longest substring should be calculated by the system.The output should be the size of the longest substring when the method public int findTheLongestSubstring(String s) is executed.